---
import InfoLayout from "../layouts/InfoLayout.astro";
---

<InfoLayout 
  title="Privacy Policy" 
  description="Privacy Policy for RePrompt - We value your privacy. RePrompt processes all image forensics client-side on your device." 
  activePath="/privacy"
>
  <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <div class="mb-12 border-b border-border/80 pb-6">
      <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground font-mono-custom">Privacy & Security</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif italic font-bold mt-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-2">Last Updated: July 3, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-foreground/90 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. Commitment to Data Privacy</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          At <strong>RePrompt</strong>, we believe that your creative assets and photographs belong to you. We are committed to maintaining the highest standards of data protection and privacy. 
        </p>
        <p>
          Unlike traditional image utilities that require you to upload your files to a remote database, RePrompt uses a modern, decentralized model where image analytics and forensics are processed locally on your device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="p-6 bg-card border border-border/60 rounded-2xl my-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-accent">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
          </svg>
          The Zero-Storage Guarantee
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          We never store, catalog, or inspect your uploaded files. All computer vision algorithms run via canvas-based metrics or local temporary buffers, which are instantly freed from memory once your forensic prompt report is generated.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. Processing Architecture</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          Our application operates using two primary tiers of analysis:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li>
            <strong>Local Computer Vision (OpenCV & Canvas):</strong> Basic structural metadata such as contrast ratio, mean brightness, Sobel gradients (for shadows), and aspect ratio are calculated directly in-memory inside your browser or temporary server buffers.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Vision-Language Models (VLM):</strong> When querying Google Gemini for prompt anatomy reconstruction, only the image bytes and isolated metrics are transmitted via a secure, encrypted API call. This information is processed statelessly and is not used for model training.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. Local Browser Storage</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          To facilitate a convenient user experience, your analysis history and performance scores (e.g., Daily Match streaks) are saved using your browser's <code>localStorage</code>.
        </p>
        <p>
          This data remains sandboxed on your device and is never synced to external databases unless explicitly requested by you. You can clear this history at any time directly through your browser settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. Third-Party Integrations</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          This site uses the Google Gemini API to analyze images and reconstruct positive and negative prompts. This integration is bound by the Google APIs Terms of Service and Privacy Policy. No other tracking scripts, advertisement networks, or data-collection pixels are active.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">5. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy or the security architecture of RePrompt, please visit our <a href="/contact" class="underline hover:text-accent">Contact Us</a> page.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</InfoLayout>
